---
title: Sweet Apple Pork Tenderloin with Cauliflower Mash and Snap Peas
description: Pork has a way of embracing fruity flavors like no other protein. In this recipe, we’re smothering it in chunks of tender, saucy apple, which adds a welcome touch of sweetness. On the side, we’ve got sugar snap peas and a potato cauliflower mash. It’s so good, no one will notice that you snuck in some extra veggies!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-apple-pork-tenderloin-6b28c207.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-apple-pork-tenderloin-35769c1e.pdf
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-apple-pork-tenderloin-598cc731ad1d6c70dc4bd282
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 320 mg
time required: 35 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch cubes. Place potatoes and half the @Cauliflower Florets{5%ounce} in a large #pot{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook until very tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot.

> We sent more cauliflower than needed.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over high heat. Season @Pork Tenderloin{12%ounce} all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Dried Thyme{1/2%tsp}. Add to pan and cook, turning, until browned all over, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Trim tough ends and strings from @Sugar Snap Peas{6%ounce}. Once pork has browned, transfer to a #baking sheet{}, placing toward one side. Add snap peas to other side and toss with a drizzle of oil and pinch of salt and pepper. Roast in oven until pork is cooked to desired doneness and snap peas are tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Halve and remove core from @Apple{1}, then chop into ½-inch cubes. Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} with a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add apple and cook until golden, ~{5-7%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup}. Increase heat to medium high and cook until apple is tender and sauce is thick, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @Butter{1%tbsp} to pot with potatoes and cauliflower. Toss to melt butter. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until mostly smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

> If potatoes and cauliflower have cooled, reheat briefly over low heat.

Slice pork into medallions. Divide cauliflower mash and snap peas between plates, then top with pork. Spoon pan sauce over pork, making sure to include apple pieces.